<paragraph blockId="10.[151,756,352,601]" pageId="10" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,284,352,375]" pageId="10" pageNumber="85">Comments:</emphasis>
This species is a member of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lobl" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[668,756,352,375]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lenta">
<emphasis box="[668,756,352,375]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="85">B. lenta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. The aedeagal characters, in particular the shape of the parameres and the comparatively simple internal sac, suggest relationships with 
<taxonomicName authority="Lobl, 2012" authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="2012" box="[482,756,449,472]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jankodadai">
<emphasis box="[482,632,449,472]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="85">B. jankodadai</emphasis>
Löbl, 2012
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[211,305,481,504]" country="Philippines" name="Palawan" pageId="10" pageNumber="85">Palawan</collectingRegion>
. The latter species differs by the comparatively short antennomere VIII and the coarse elytral punctation not extending onto apical third of elytral disc.
</paragraph>
